## 3. JSON Schemas

### 3a. Agent 1 Output — IntentSpec

```json
{
  "$schema": "IntentSpec",
  "query": "Help me understand how neural networks work",
  "intent": "explanation",
  "domain": "machine-learning",
  "complexity": "intermediate",
  "goalType": "understand",
  "requiredInputs": [],
  "contextFromChat": []
}
```

**`goalType`** enum: `"understand"` | `"decide"` | `"analyze"` | `"create"` | `"compare"` | `"learn"`

**`requiredInputs`**: array of `{ "type": "csv" | "text" | "selection", "label": string, "description": string }` — what the system needs from the user before it can generate.

### 3b. Agent 2 Output — UXPlan

```json
{
  "$schema": "UXPlan",
  "experienceType": "wiki",
  "layout": "single-column",
  "sections": [
    { "role": "hero", "purpose": "Visual hook + title" },
    { "role": "content", "purpose": "Core explanation with visuals" },
    { "role": "interactive", "purpose": "Try-it-yourself simulation" },
    { "role": "summary", "purpose": "Key takeaways" }
  ],
  "interactionModel": "scroll-through",
  "estimatedBlocks": 8
}
```

**`experienceType`** enum: `"quiz"` | `"dashboard"` | `"wiki"` | `"form"` | `"comparison"` | `"slides"` | `"hybrid"`

**`interactionModel`** enum: `"scroll-through"` | `"step-by-step"` | `"tabbed"` | `"interactive"`

### 3c. Agent 3 Output — UISpec (the core schema)

```json
{
  "$schema": "UISpec",
  "version": "1.0",
  "title": "How Neural Networks Work",
  "theme": { "accent": "#2563eb" },
  "root": {
    "type": "Stack",
    "props": { "gap": "lg" },
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "Hero",
        "props": {
          "title": "Neural Networks",
          "subtitle": "From biological neurons to artificial intelligence",
          "visual": "brain-network"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "WikiSection",
        "props": {
          "heading": "What is a Neural Network?",
          "body": "A neural network is a computing system inspired by...",
          "aside": {
            "type": "InfoCard",
            "props": {
              "title": "Key Insight",
              "content": "Every neural network is just matrix multiplication + activation functions."
            }
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "Tabs",
        "props": {
          "tabs": ["Perceptron", "Deep Networks", "CNNs"]
        },
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "WikiSection",
            "props": { "heading": "The Perceptron", "body": "..." }
          },
          {
            "type": "WikiSection",
            "props": { "heading": "Deep Networks", "body": "..." }
          },
          {
            "type": "WikiSection",
            "props": { "heading": "CNNs", "body": "..." }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "Quiz",
        "props": {
          "questions": [
            {
              "question": "What does an activation function do?",
              "options": ["Stores data", "Introduces non-linearity", "Compresses images"],
              "correct": 1
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The UISpec is a **recursive tree structure**. Every node has `type` (from the allowlist), `props` (type-specific), and optional `children` (array of nodes). This is how nesting works — a `Tabs` block can contain `WikiSection` blocks, which can contain `InfoCard` blocks, etc.

