## 7. Rendering Strategy

### Dynamic Renderer (recursive component mapper)

```tsx
// Pseudocode for the core renderer
function BlockRenderer({ node }) {
  const Component = BLOCK_REGISTRY[node.type]
  if (!Component) return <UnknownBlock type={node.type} />

  const children = node.children?.map((child, i) => (
    <BlockRenderer key={i} node={child} />
  ))

  return <Component {...node.props}>{children}</Component>
}

// Usage
<BlockRenderer node={uiSpec.root} />
```

### State Machine for Generation Flow

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Idle
    Idle --> Streaming : user submits query
    Streaming --> IntentParsed : Agent 1 complete
    IntentParsed --> NeedsInput : requiredInputs not empty
    NeedsInput --> Streaming : user provides input
    IntentParsed --> UXPlanned : Agent 2 complete
    UXPlanned --> Rendering : Agent 3 streaming
    Rendering --> Complete : UISpec validated
    Complete --> Conversational : chat unlocked
    Conversational --> Streaming : follow-up query
    Streaming --> Error : validation failure
    Error --> Idle : user dismisses
```

### SSE Streaming Protocol

The `/api/generate` endpoint streams events to the client:

```
event: status
data: {"stage": "intent", "message": "Understanding your query..."}

event: status
data: {"stage": "ux", "message": "Designing the best experience..."}

event: status
data: {"stage": "rendering", "message": "Building your interactive experience..."}

event: spec
data: {"type": "partial", "blocks": 3, "total": 8}

event: complete
data: { ... full UISpec JSON ... }

event: error
data: {"message": "Failed to generate experience", "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR"}
```

