## 8. Data Model

Since data is ephemeral (no persistence), the "data model" exists only in-memory during a session. However, we define the shapes for when persistence is added later.

### Session (in-memory)

```ts
interface Session {
  id: string
  userId: string          // from OAuth
  messages: Message[]     // chat history
  currentSpec: UISpec | null
  pipeline: PipelineState
  createdAt: Date
}

interface Message {
  id: string
  role: 'user' | 'system' | 'status'
  content: string
  timestamp: Date
  metadata?: { stage?: string, spec?: UISpec }
}

interface PipelineState {
  status: 'idle' | 'running' | 'complete' | 'error'
  currentStage: 'intent' | 'ux' | 'rendering' | null
  intentSpec: IntentSpec | null
  uxPlan: UXPlan | null
  uiSpec: UISpec | null
  error: string | null
}
```

### User Profile (future — stored in DB)

```ts
interface UserProfile {
  id: string
  email: string
  name: string
  provider: 'google' | 'github'
  preferences: {
    theme: 'light' | 'dark'
    complexity: 'basic' | 'intermediate' | 'advanced'
    favoriteTopics: string[]
  }
  createdAt: Date
}
```

