## Key Design Decisions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Why three agents instead of one?** Separation of concerns allows independent iteration. The intent agent can be swapped for a fine-tuned classifier later. The UX selector can incorporate user preferences. The renderer can be optimized per-experience-type. It's slower now but architecturally sound.

> [!NOTE]
> **Why Zod over JSON Schema?** Zod gives us TypeScript-native validation with type inference — one schema defines both the runtime validator and the TypeScript type. No separate type definitions to keep in sync.

> [!NOTE]
> **Why SSE over WebSockets?** SSE is simpler, HTTP-native, works through CDNs/proxies without configuration, and is perfectly suited for our unidirectional server→client streaming pattern. WebSockets would be overkill.

